 What We are Watching

 Theatre

 Bharatkatha

 Weaving Chattisgarhi Teejan Bais Pandavani format with Purulias jhumur folk form, this play by Kasba Arghya picks the war episode from the Mahabharata for a contemporary representation. Seema Ghosh gives a brilliant performance as a Pandavani.

 Watch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm, October 29

 Mirror... Mirror 

 Written and directed by Anindita Sarbadhicary. With minimum props, the act focuses on Anindita and actress Shahana Chatterjee sharing notes on the mirror and the power it has had over them since childhood, revealing tales of tormented self-image. 

 Watch it at Padatik Buildwell 

 Theatre, 6.30 pm, October 28 and 29

 Page 4

 Playwright and director Bratya Basus take on the world of celebrities, cultural dos, award ceremonies and power equations, Page 4 is presented by Lok Krishti. 

 Watch it at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm, October 28




